The paper discusses microarchitectural attacks and defenses on commodity systems, which are typically related to computer security (cs.CR) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also mentions the use of sandboxed JavaScript code in websites, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the attacks on modern computer systems, including mobile devices and commercial cloud systems, which are related to systems and networking (cs.SY).
